  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (15204ec 2022-11-29T00:04:59.199031Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge fmt\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n`forge init` a new project and update `setNumber` as follows:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction setNumber(uint256 newNumber, uint256 sjdfasdfasdfasdfasfsdfsadfasdfasdfasdfsadjfkhasdfljkahsdfkjasdkfhsaf) public { // forgefmt: disable-line\r\n    number = newNumber;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBasically, we just give one arg a really long var name to force it over the line width, then add the `forgefmt: disable-line` comment. Now run `forge fmt` and you get this:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction setNumber(uint256 newNumber, uint256 sjdfasdfasdfasdfasfsdfsadfasdfasdfasdfsadjfkhasdfljkahsdfkjasdkfhsaf)\r\n    public\r\n{\r\n// forgefmt: disable-line\r\n    number = newNumber;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNotice how the `disable-line` statement was ignoredâ€”`public` and `forgefmt: disable-line` both were moved onto their own lines",
